      "message": "When you’re implementing something that comes from some interface:\n\n1. We usually have a comment saying what interface it comes from.\n2. Say “override,” which gives you a little compiler checking, plus another hint that this is an interface method.\n\nSo:\n\n private:\n  // Thread:\n  void ThreadMain() override {\n\nSame for CatchMachException on line 143.\n\nBoth of these are things that we’d do at the class declaration, so if you split things between a .h and .cc, I’d expect to see these in the .h. (I don’t mean that you need a split here. I’m just giving helpful advice. I hope.)",
      "revId": "9f4b9d892532481994c06d20b08436ed6e158fe5",
